oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Medals of Sgt. James A. White, Co. A, 115th FA
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Sgt. James A. White was from Bells, Tenn. and served in Co. A, 1st Tenn. NG on the Mexican Border in 1917. After the NG was transferred to federal service he served in Btry. A, 115th FA, 30th Div. The medals include Mexican Border Service issued by Tenn., a Mexican Border private purchase medal with listings of soliders on the reverse; Mexican Border medal issued by the City of Memphis; his WWI Victory Medal and WWI service medal from the City of Nashville. The group includes dog tags, collar disk, button.
